txt.en: Head into the Ettenmoors and collect the materials that are needed to reinforce the gate at Lugazag.
'The gate is not reinforcing itself, and I do not see what I need in your hands. So fill up those hands with what I asked for, or I will lop them off.'
You are directed back into the wilds of the Ettenmoors to collect material needed to reinforce the gate at Lugazag.

'You done good so far. The enemy is foolish enough to keep throwing bodies at the walls and the gate. If we do not reinforce the gate, they may break through. That would make the war-tyrant angry. We do not want the war-tyrant angry, yes?

'So you are going back out into the wilderness to get more of what we need to make the gate sturdy. Sturdy like the war-tyrant himself. Got it?

'Go!'
Deliver the materials to Dum√ªl at Lugazag
'You did good following the request I made. Now I will hold up my end of the bargain and strengthen the gate. We will hold this tower away from the enemy!'
Defence: Reinforce the Gate at Lugazag
